Apply a Dashboard Filter

Filter a dashboard to analyze the information interactively. After you filter a dashboard, the filtered view is preserved so that the next time you see the dashboard, data is filtered in the same view.

Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

User Permissions Needed:
To view, refresh, and apply filters to dashboards that you created: Run Reports
To view, refresh, and apply filters to dashboards in public folders: Run Reports AND View Dashboards in Public Folders

Open a dashboard.
Select a dashboard filter from the dropdown list.
Each filter has one or more options that you can choose to narrow your selection.
To see data unfiltered, select Clear Filter or All.
title: Apply Filters to Salesforce Dashboards
